Stewart Rome https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stewart_Rome 0 Stewart Rome (born Septimus William Ryott, January 30, 1886 – February 26, 1965) was an English actor who appeared in more than 150 films between 1913 and 1950. He was born in Newbury, Berkshire in 1886 and took the stage name of Stewart Rome, which was later unsuccessfully contested by Cecil Hepworth, who also used the name. He became a major star in the silent era.
